  "couName": "Non-cannulated F1717 compression-bending",
  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. A screening sensitivity exercise was conducted during model development to rank the relative influence of titanium alloy elastic modulus, cortical bone thickness, and fixation torque on predicted construct stiffness; results confirmed that modulus dominated with a normalized sensitivity index of 0.71. Because this screening was performed informally as part of model calibration and not structured as a standalone SensitivityAnalysis activity, it is described here in narrative form only and is not linked as a formal sensitivity analysis node.",
