      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V modeled with bilinear isotropic hardening (E=114 GPa, σ_y=880 MPa, Et=1.5 GPa) consistent with published mechanical characterization data. Augmented Lagrangian contact formulation applied at screw-rod and screw-vertebral body block interfaces. Model form uncertainty assessed as low given the quasi-static, isothermal loading regime."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from traceable coupon testing or peer-reviewed literature; geometric inputs derived from CMM measurements of test articles.",
      "rationale": "Titanium alloy material properties were drawn from ASTM F136-13 and supplemented by in-house tensile coupon testing (n=5). Screw and rod geometry inputs were derived from coordinate measuring machine (CMM) measurements of production hardware to within ±0.02 mm. UHMWPE vertebral body block properties were taken from manufacturer data sheets with literature cross-check."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
