      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs were tested across two independent laboratories (Lab 1: n=6, Lab 2: n=5). All hardware was sourced from production lots with full traceability to the device master record. UHMWPE vertebral body blocks were supplied by a certified vendor meeting ASTM F648 requirements."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Testing conducted under multiple clinically relevant loading rates and environmental conditions; laboratory-to-laboratory variability characterized.",
      "rationale": "Testing was performed at a single quasi-static loading rate (5 mm/min) per ASTM F1717. Although inter-laboratory reproducibility was demonstrated (CV < 5% for stiffness), the absence of multiple loading rates and environmental conditions (e.g., simulated body fluid, elevated temperature) limits this factor to Gradation 2. This shortfall is acknowledged and is the one factor below required level; its impact is bounded by the conservative acceptance criteria applied."
    },
